# .StataEnviron -- project-local paths, loaded by `statareport_load_env'.
#
# Copy this file to `.StataEnviron' (gitignored) at the project root and
# fill in the values for your machine. Every KEY=VALUE line below becomes
# the Stata global $dir_<key> (lowercased) when statareport_load_env
# runs at the top of your master do-file.
#
# Also accepted:
#   - shell-style `#` comments and blank lines
#   - optional `export ` prefix
#   - single- or double-quoted values
#   - any `STATAREPORT_<NAME>` key from the operating system environment

# --- Shared cloud folder (OneDrive / SharePoint / Dropbox / ...) ---------
# ONEDRIVE=/Users/you/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-YourOrg

# --- Raw dataset export (feeds statareport_set_data_root) ----------------
# DATASETS=/Users/you/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-YourOrg/Dataset_export/<YYYY-MM>/Stata

# --- Project root override (rarely needed; `here' finds it by default) ---
# PROJECT=/Users/you/projects/
